I suspect we've done this (I suspect _I've_ done this) but
suppose way back in 1985, the PTB at DC comics look at the idea of
CoIE and think &quot;there is no way that this can result in anything but
a giant snarl of contradictory continuity&quot; and reject the idea of
collapsing all of the alternate Earths in the DCU into one.

Upside: a lot of comics whose basis was undermined by CoIE
survive in a healthier form.

I suspect it won't touch some of the problems superhero
comics have&quot; the slide into grimngritty, the rise of some truly
shitty artstyles, the inevitable decline in sales. On the plus side,
Legion of Superheroes would probably have suffered, if not less at
least differently in the last generation.

Actually, what might have been an interesting idea is to do an
Earth-naught: just as Earth 1 had all its heroes begin 25 years later
than their analogs on E2, E0 is the story of an Earth whose masks are
just starting out. That's a cleaner slate with meta connections to the
old continuities and it might allow more interesting work.
